HEADWORD: Lichenic
<hw>Li*chen"ic</hw> <pr>(l⟦isl⟧*k⟦ecr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or obtained from, lichens.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lichenic acid</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>An organic
acid, <chform>C14H24O3</chform>, obtained from Iceland moss.</cd>
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>An old name of fumaric acid.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Licheniform</ent>⟦br⟧
